title: Album Page, "Traced Profile of Baluster from Loggia at Château Blois, France", late 19th century
medium: Graphite on very smooth, off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, bottom right corner (perpendicular to drawing): 110. Verso, in graphite, left face of sheet (as bound): 117; right face of sheet (as bound): Baluster of logia [sic] at Chateau de Blois.
dimensions: Sheet: 39.1 x 30.7 cm (15 3/8 x 12 1/16 in.), irregular
description: Vertical sheet folded and tipped into binding so that bottom edge of drawing space is the right side of sheet as bound.  Depicted is a traced profile of a baluster.
